@node "Hist" "History"

                                   @{b}@{fg shine}History@{fg text}@{ub}

@{fg shine}v1.22@{fg text} - Sixth Aminet release
@{fg  fill}Change:@{fg text} Window remains active when Configuration needs it's closing
@{fg  fill}Change:@{fg text} Code changed, some tiny bugs and possible bugs fixed

@{fg shine}v1.20@{fg text} - Fifth Aminet release
@{fg  fill}Change:@{fg text} Now uses NewLookMenus
@{fg shine}   New:@{fg text} Localisation
@{fg shine}   New:@{fg text} HH:MM/HH:MM:SS time display
@{fg shine}   New:@{fg text} Ability to lock window on screen, so that it can't be moved
@{fg shine}   New:@{fg text} CyberClock.guide is now fully OpenURL compliant :)
@{fg shine}   New:@{fg text} @{"ReInstall feature" link "ReIn"}

@{fg shine}v1.12@{fg text} - Fourth Aminet release

Bugfix: PowerSnap now works properly with CyberClock
@{fg shine}   New:@{fg text} 12/24hrs time display (requested by Andrew Clark)

@{fg shine}v1.10@{fg text} - Third Aminet release

@{fg  fill}Change:@{fg text} CLI arguments now work normally
@{fg  fill}Change:@{fg text} Code rewritten from scratch, again shorter and faster
@{fg  fill}Change:@{fg text} Added @{b}DONOTWAIT@{ub} tooltype in icon
@{fg shine}   New:@{fg text} Info requester shown if digits brush cannot be opened
@{fg shine}   New:@{fg text} Support for screennotify.library . CyberClock closes/opens it's window
itself when Workbench screen is closed/opened. This works fine with FastIPrefs
and notifyintuition.library too.

@{fg shine}v1.03@{fg text} - Second Aminet release

Bugfix: Doesn't crash system if told to use nonexisting digits brush
Bugfix: Test CyberClock script now works properly
@{fg  fill}Change:@{fg text} Current day and date are now displayed in screen titlebar
@{fg  fill}Change:@{fg text} Some functions changed, shorter and faster code

@{fg shine}v1.00@{fg text} - Initial Aminet release

@endnode
