@{fg shine}Distribution:@{fg text}

CyberClock is an @{"emailware" link "Regs"} program, and, as such, you can freely distribute
it, providing that all files in it's archive are left intact. You can @{b}not@{ub}
distribute CyberClock, or any other file from it's archive separately from
other files.

You can put it on public domain disk or include it in public domain disk
library, @{b}only@{ub} if you do not charge it with too high copying fee.

You can put it on a PD software compilation (such as Aminet CD), or magazine
coverdisk, @{b}only@{ub} if you send a note to the @{"author" link "Auth"} stating that you
have done it. You don't need author's permission, nor reply.

You can include it in commercial package or commercial program collection, 
@{b}only@{ub} with a written permission from the @{"author" link "Auth"}.

