@node "ReIn" "ReInstallation"

                               @{b}@{fg shine}ReInstallation@{fg text}@{ub}

ReInstallation is a new concept I have added to CyberClock, to my knowledge
not used by any program before. @{b}Install CyberClock@{ub} script writes data about
destinations of CyberClock executable and documentation in file
@{b}S:CyberClock.reinstall@{ub}. When you are updating your CyberClock, instead of
specifying that destinations again and again, you should just use @{b}ReInstall
CyberClock@{ub} script which will copy new versions of executable and
documentation to their proper destinations, without bothering you at all. I
hope that this concept will spread to all programs where change of install
parameters is unlikely to occure while updating :)

@endnode
